ion but I should verify whether the 備考 column information about maximum string lengths is still being preserved accurately. Looking at the complete list of character types from the test case table, I can see all eleven categories are accounted for: half-width alphanumeric and symbols, half-width katakana, full-width variants across all character types, and external characters. The duplicate half-width number entry in the source is likely a data entry error.\n\nChecking the knowledge file against the source code, the `testSingleValidation` method example is properly documented, and the reference links in section 2 appear to be correctly formatted. The documentation seems comprehensive and accurate overall. Looking at the source more carefully, I see the test case names are slightly different from what the knowledge file captured—the source says \"精査のテストケース\" and \"コンストラクタのテストケース\" while the knowledge file simplified these to \"精査テストケース\" and \"コンストラクタテストケース\"—but the mapping is close enough that it's not a real issue. The Java code example for the test class itself isn't captured in the knowledge file, though that's fine since the substantive rules are there. I'm also noticing a duplicate character type entry in the source table that looks like a typo, which the knowledge file handled reasonably by consolidating the entries.\n\nThe knowledge file appears quite solid overall. The source's navigation links and download references are appropriately excluded, and I've verified that the footnote about `messageIdWhenInvalidLength` defaults is properly captured in the s3 table.\n\nFor `messageIdWhenEmptyInput`, the knowledge file correctly summarizes the source's note about using the `emptyInputMessageIdの値` from the configuration when omitted.\n\nNow I'm checking the s4 section more carefully against the source to make sure the test data table is accurately represented. Looking at how the source table structures the notes column, it seems the annotation about character type